Date: Sun, 14 Jun 2026 23:39:16 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] exif gps parsing: fix integer overflow

With hight-precision denominator (10000000), computation
of seconds in gps coordinates leads to integer overflow.
This is the minimal fix, upstream fixes this bug
in 8c6e8b139 with bigger refactoring related to gexiv2
migration.
---
 src/extractor/utils/tracker-exif.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/extractor/utils/tracker-exif.c b/src/extractor/utils/tracker-exif.c
index 995456856..2b4cb3e5a 100644
--- a/src/extractor/utils/tracker-exif.c
+++ b/src/extractor/utils/tracker-exif.c
@@ -328,8 +328,8 @@ get_gps_coordinate (ExifData *exif,
 			}
 
 			f = (gdouble) degrees.numerator / degrees.denominator +
-				(gdouble) minutes.numerator / (minutes.denominator * 60) +
-				(gdouble) seconds.numerator / (seconds.denominator * 60 * 60);
+				(gdouble) minutes.numerator / ((gdouble)minutes.denominator * 60.0) +
+				(gdouble) seconds.numerator / ((gdouble)seconds.denominator * 60.0 * 60.0);
 
 			if (refentry->format != EXIF_FORMAT_ASCII || refentry->size < 2) {
 				g_debug ("Invalid format/size for GPS ref entry");
-- 
2.51.0

